# Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the root directory with the following variables:

```
REACT_APP_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url
REACT_APP_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
```

## Getting Supabase Credentials

1. Go to [supabase.com](https://supabase.com) and create a new project
2. In your project dashboard, go to Settings > API
3. Copy the Project URL and anon/public key
4. Replace the placeholder values in your `.env` file

## Database Setup

1. Run the SQL schema from `supabase-schema.sql` in your Supabase SQL editor
2. This will create all necessary tables, functions, and policies
3. Enable Row Level Security (RLS) is already configured in the schema

## FingerprintJS Setup

The application uses FingerprintJS v4 which is free and open-source. No API key is required for basic functionality.

For production use, consider upgrading to FingerprintJS Pro for better accuracy and fraud detection capabilities.
